title: Appointment of Chairman to the Veterinary Surgeons Board of Hong Kong
content_text:
p>
			The Government announced today (September 13) the appointment of 
			Professor Ching Pak-chung as Chairman of the Veterinary Surgeons 
			Board of Hong Kong (VSB) for three years from September 15, 2013 to 
			September 14, 2016. Professor Ching is the Pro-Vice-Chancellor/Vice-President and 
			Professor of Electronic Engineering of the Chinese University of 
			Hong Kong (CUHK). He also serves as Director of CUHK Shenzhen

Hong Kong (CUHK). He also serves as Director of CUHK Shenzhen 
			Research Institute. Professor Ching is currently Chairman of the 
			Hong Kong Council for Testing and Certification and a member of the 
			Steering Committee on Innovation and Technology. The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, thanked Professor 
			Ching for accepting the appointment. He is confident that Professor 
			Ching will continue to uphold high veterinary standards in Hong Kong

Ching will continue to uphold high veterinary standards in Hong Kong 
			and lead the VSB to scale new heights. Dr Ko also expressed his gratitude to the outgoing Chairman, 
			Professor Wong Yuk-shan, for his distinguished leadership and 
			immense contribution during his term of appointment. Dr Ko commended 
			Professor Wong for his drive and passion, which help the furtherance 
			of VSB's mission in safeguarding the health and welfare of animals

of VSB's mission in safeguarding the health and welfare of animals 
			and the interests of animal owners. Enacted in 1997, the Veterinary Surgeons Registration Ordinance (Cap 
			529) provides for the establishment of the VSB, which is responsible 
			for the regulation of the practice of veterinary surgery, the 
			registration of veterinary surgeons and the disciplinary control of 
			the professional activities of registered veterinary surgeons in 
			Hong Kong.
